Privacy Policy
Privacy Policy for the Binary Family Games
Last Updated: October 26, 2023
This Privacy Policy describes how the Binary Family collects, uses, and protects your information when you use our games.
1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following information:
Device information (e.g., operating system, device type).
Game usage data (e.g., game play time, scores).
Your IP address.
Any information you provide voluntarily (e.g., in surveys).
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information to:
Improve our games.
Personalize your experience.
Provide customer support.
Analyze trends and usage patterns.
3. Information Sharing
We do not share your personal information with third parties except as necessary for providing our services or with your consent.
4. Security
We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure.
5. Your Choices
You have the right to access, correct, or delete your personal information.  Please contact us at
support@thebinaryfamily.com
to exercise these rights.
6. Childrenâ€™s Privacy
Our games are not directed to children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
7. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at
support@thebinaryfamily.com
.